Credits & attribution
==============================================================================

PromptWise orchestrates and interoperates with the following open-source
agentic-development frameworks and standards. PromptWise does not bundle their
source; it recommends, references, and is designed to wire them as optional
backends. Each remains under its own license and copyright.

- BMAD-METHOD            — MIT License            — https://github.com/bmad-code-org/BMAD-METHOD
- GitHub Spec Kit        — OSS (see project)      — https://github.com/github/spec-kit
- OpenSpec               — OSS (see project)      — https://github.com/Fission-AI/OpenSpec
- TaskMaster             — OSS (see project)      — https://github.com/eyaltoledano/claude-task-master
- Model Context Protocol — open standard          — https://modelcontextprotocol.io
- AGENTS.md              — open convention         — https://agents.md

If you wrap or redistribute any of the above as a backend, retain their LICENSE
files and attribution. Star counts and adoption figures referenced in docs are
as of mid-2026 and will drift — re-verify before relying on them.
